      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COCO MAC (1) has a strong record this trip with nine wins and five placings from 21 starts. Was out of placings last time (18.47) at this track in a Grade 3/4, finishing fourth and beaten 4 lengths. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. KIANDO DIVA (2) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at Temora over 330m behind Kiando Hunt (20.17) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Shapes as one to consider. TAMARAMA BEACH (8) jumped well from the low draw and led all the way to score last start (19.80) at Gunnedah in a Grade 5 over 340m. One of the key runners again. SOUTHBROOK MERV (5) has won at this course and distance, should be thereabouts.",
